<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,1285,1802]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1285,1311]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frons deep yellow; fronto-orbital plate deep golden pollinose; antenna with postpedicel about 4.5 times the length of pedicel; palpus yellowish-white, scutum brownish-grey pollinose; legs yellow; wing clear in female, but with a brown spot at apex of vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[768,794,1376,1390]" fontSize="6" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
2+ 
<quantity box="[786,794,1376,1390]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="in" value="3.0">3</quantity>
</subScript>
in male. Abdomen in female: syntergite 1+2 yellow, tergites 3–4 with three brown spots, tergite 5 grey, with 2 brown spots. Abdomen in male: syntergite 1+2 and tergite 3 yellow, tergites 4 and 5 grey with three brown spots. Abdomen strongly modified in male; compressed laterally; tergite 5 with a median keel, with a tuft of long setae and ventrally with strong black setae on each side (Fig. 47 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Crosskey, R. W." box="[501,685,1515,1541]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="393 - 551" refId="ref53854" refString="Crosskey, R. W. (1962) A revision of the genus Pygophora Schiner (Diptera, Muscidae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London, 29, 393 - 551." type="journal article" year="1962">Crosskey, 1962</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,1285,1802]" box="[198,940,1552,1578]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
No material of this species has been seen from 
<collectingCountry box="[750,936,1552,1578]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,1285,1802]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,341,1589,1615]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Curran, C. H." box="[354,526,1590,1616]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref53890" refString="Curran, C. H. (1929) Diptera collected by Prof. and Mrs. Cockerell in New Caledonia and Fiji Islands. American Museum Novitates, 375, 1 - 15." type="journal article" year="1929">Curran (1929)</bibRefCitation>
recorded a single male from Mueo, but the record was not accepted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Crosskey, R. W." box="[151,346,1627,1653]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="393 - 551" refId="ref53854" refString="Crosskey, R. W. (1962) A revision of the genus Pygophora Schiner (Diptera, Muscidae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London, 29, 393 - 551." type="journal article" year="1962">Crosskey (1962)</bibRefCitation>
who recognized the species only from the Oriental Region and Melanesia. The species was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Crosskey, R. W." box="[346,560,1664,1690]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="393 - 551" refId="ref53854" refString="Crosskey, R. W. (1962) A revision of the genus Pygophora Schiner (Diptera, Muscidae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London, 29, 393 - 551." type="journal article" year="1962">Crosskey (1962)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinonaga, S. &amp; Kano, R. &amp; Fauran, P." box="[574,874,1664,1690]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="329 - 334" refId="ref57937" refString="Shinonaga, S., Kano, R. &amp; Fauran, P. (1991) Muscid flies of New Caledonia, with description of a new species (Diptera, Muscidae). In: Chazeau, J. &amp; Tillier, S. (eds), Zoologia Neocaledonica, Volume 2. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, (A), 149, 329 - 334." type="journal article" year="1991">
Shinonaga 
<emphasis box="[716,773,1665,1690]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">et al</emphasis>
. (1991)
</bibRefCitation>
did not mention this species. Curran’s 
<collectingCountry name="New Caledonia" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
material has not been found in AMNH.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
